1
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:07,066
<The dream that caused a woman to fall to her death>

2
00:00:07,066 --> 00:00:09,660
<The woman's only daughter Mio>

3
00:00:09,660 --> 00:00:11,660
(Mio) I don't know if it was suicide or not.

4
00:00:11,660 --> 00:00:14,198
(Yume) The true identity of the person who may have been pushed down.

5
00:00:14,198 --> 00:00:16,099
What if we quickly find out?

6
00:00:16,099 --> 00:00:20,693
< 100 million yen in damages while the forbidden friendship deepens

7
00:00:20,693 --> 00:00:26,396
Two witnesses to the discovery of their lover's affair are forced into further confinement.

8
00:00:26,396 --> 00:00:29,396
(Sakuma) I might have made a mistake.

9
00:00:32,594 --> 00:00:38,000
(breathing heavily)

10
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:40,066
《It can't be helped, since they saw it.》

11
00:00:40,066 --> 00:00:42,627
``So what's the point of bringing her here? 》

12
00:00:42,627 --> 00:00:47,726
《So I thought I would discuss it with you》

13
00:00:47,726 --> 00:00:50,528
《Did you hit me? 》 《Huh? No, I haven't...》

14
00:00:50,528 --> 00:00:52,957
``Then why is it freezing?'' That person》

15
00:00:52,957 --> 00:00:55,825
♬(Hashimoto)《We are dead》

16
00:00:55,825 --> 00:01:01,462
♬《We are dead, we are dead》

17
00:01:01,462 --> 00:01:05,363
♬《I went to heaven》

18
00:01:05,363 --> 00:01:08,891
♬《Long stairs》

19
00:01:08,891 --> 00:01:14,858
(Kayoko) Where has your father gone already?

20
00:01:14,858 --> 00:01:20,693
Ah, this is yes, yes, yes, ah, contact information.

21
00:01:20,693 --> 00:01:23,825
I want to thank you properly this time, so I won't say that at all...

22
00:01:23,825 --> 00:01:28,495
Kairiki Moving Center Gymnast

23
00:01:28,495 --> 00:01:30,363
♬We are dead

24
00:01:30,363 --> 00:01:33,627
Ah, are you a moving company?

25
00:01:33,627 --> 00:01:39,330
Ah... I'm really sorry for bothering you, but I'm late as well.

26
00:01:39,330 --> 00:01:44,726
Sorry, this is it... Dad too (Hashimoto) Ah...

27
00:01:46,429 --> 00:01:50,594
(Hashimoto) “Hey, you, right in the middle of heaven.

28
00:01:50,594 --> 00:01:56,528
You're so naive. You should be more serious."

29
00:01:56,528 --> 00:02:00,429
(Kayoko) Dad! Sorry, yes, it's okay

30
00:02:00,429 --> 00:02:04,198
♬(Hashimoto) We are dead.

31
00:02:06,033 --> 00:02:09,660
Receipt huh?

32
00:02:11,528 --> 00:02:14,363
(sound of things falling)

33
00:02:14,363 --> 00:02:19,264
Okay, receipt.

34
00:02:33,627 --> 00:02:35,627
sorry

35
00:02:40,099 --> 00:02:45,594
I've always wanted to say it someday

36
00:02:45,594 --> 00:02:51,924
"Someday, forever" is a contradiction, isn't it?

37
00:02:51,924 --> 00:02:53,924
sorry

38
00:03:03,825 --> 00:03:07,000
I didn't want my wife to find out.

39
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:10,858
Is that why you said you should run away?

40
00:03:15,561 --> 00:03:21,297
I'll think about it properly...

41
00:03:25,858 --> 00:03:28,495
What about children?

42
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:39,594
obstacle!

43
00:03:49,462 --> 00:03:54,264
I know it really sucks (cell phone vibrating sound)

44
00:03:54,264 --> 00:03:56,264
but…

45
00:03:58,099 --> 00:04:04,759
I didn't want to tell you the truth and hurt you.

46
00:04:07,297 --> 00:04:12,330
It's like breaking someone's bones and giving them a bandage.

47
00:04:12,330 --> 00:04:14,330
Huh?

48
00:04:15,858 --> 00:04:19,066
We're the worst.

49
00:04:26,363 --> 00:04:31,891
Let's end this, we'll hurt a lot of people.

50
00:04:31,891 --> 00:04:35,429
Dream... I'll forget everything

51
00:04:35,429 --> 00:04:38,792
So Kenken too...

52
00:04:41,165 --> 00:04:45,528
Please do the same, Sakuma-san.

53
00:05:20,297 --> 00:05:40,297
♬〜

54
00:05:40,297 --> 00:05:44,033
♬〜

55
00:05:47,693 --> 00:05:59,528
♬〜

56
00:05:59,528 --> 00:06:01,825
I don't remember

57
00:06:01,825 --> 00:06:08,000
So you don't remember if there was another person on the roof?

58
00:06:09,363 --> 00:06:12,033
(Endo) If your husband remembers something again.

59
00:06:12,033 --> 00:06:15,792
Please contact us anytime

60
00:06:15,792 --> 00:06:21,066
Does that mean anything? Huh?

61
00:06:21,066 --> 00:06:23,858
(Sae) We also want to finish it quickly.

62
00:06:23,858 --> 00:06:27,198
We are also proceeding with the procedure to claim compensation for damages.

63
00:06:27,198 --> 00:06:28,858
ah…

64
00:06:28,858 --> 00:06:32,561
After a lot of investigation, they decided not to reopen the investigation.

65
00:06:32,561 --> 00:06:37,231
You said you were relieved by suicide, right?

66
00:06:37,231 --> 00:06:40,726
100 million. Damages.

67
00:06:40,726 --> 00:06:44,132
If this continues, I will have no choice but to renounce the inheritance.

68
00:06:44,132 --> 00:06:49,429
Then I would lose everything, including my house.

69
00:06:49,429 --> 00:06:53,825
As I said earlier, in the end, Mr. Kondo also

70
00:06:53,825 --> 00:06:56,858
You said you don't remember very well.

71
00:06:56,858 --> 00:07:01,396
So please look me in the eye and tell me

72
00:07:01,396 --> 00:07:04,231
yes? Mr. Endo

73
00:07:04,231 --> 00:07:07,528
There was definitely no one on the roof.

74
00:07:07,528 --> 00:07:09,528
If you could look me in the eye and say it one more time

75
00:07:09,528 --> 00:07:12,561
I'm giving up, Osako-san...

76
00:07:12,561 --> 00:07:15,660
I think it was a mistake to forcefully enter the building the other day.

77
00:07:15,660 --> 00:07:20,264
But I still don't know what really happened that day.

78
00:07:20,264 --> 00:07:24,891
I just can't accept losing my house and everything.

79
00:07:39,726 --> 00:07:43,297
(Ring tone)

80
00:07:43,297 --> 00:07:46,528
📱(Taro) Hello, sister?

81
00:07:46,528 --> 00:07:49,660
Hello, where are you now?

82
00:07:49,660 --> 00:07:53,561
📱(Taro) What? Confinement?

83
00:07:53,561 --> 00:07:58,297
📱That's not right. Oh, I'm sorry. Are you your sister?

84
00:07:58,297 --> 00:08:00,957
What is confinement? 📱That's not true.

85
00:08:00,957 --> 00:08:02,924
📱Can I have you come and pick me up?

86
00:08:02,924 --> 00:08:08,627
📱My younger brother is here now and his name is Osako.

87
00:08:08,627 --> 00:08:11,462
Huh?

88
00:08:11,462 --> 00:08:13,825
Huh? what? younger brother?

89
00:08:13,825 --> 00:08:15,495
Huh? Huh? Is that your younger brother? You

90
00:08:15,495 --> 00:08:17,792
(Sakura) I seriously don't care.

91
00:08:17,792 --> 00:08:20,759
The person relationship diagram

92
00:08:20,759 --> 00:08:31,330
♬〜

93
00:08:31,330 --> 00:08:35,957
(Taro) Excuse me, can I get some shichimi?

94
00:08:45,561 --> 00:08:49,066
Ah, I'd rather have my own crew.

95
00:08:49,066 --> 00:08:52,297
If it's about compensation for damages, I'll take care of it from now on...

96
00:08:52,297 --> 00:08:57,858
Lie, can't you pay? 100 million, that's...

97
00:08:57,858 --> 00:09:02,528
I can't pay, but I'll give up my inheritance and run away.

98
00:09:02,528 --> 00:09:07,627
What are you doing here?

99
00:09:07,627 --> 00:09:09,429
It's just a suggestion

100
00:09:09,429 --> 00:09:13,132
Aunt, will you pay me 1 million yen?

101
00:09:13,132 --> 00:09:14,792
Huh? 1 million?

102
00:09:14,792 --> 00:09:16,462
Huh? Not my parents

103
00:09:16,462 --> 00:09:20,561
If you pay me 1 million yen, I will give you 100 million yen in damages and withdraw it.

104
00:09:20,561 --> 00:09:23,462
100 million to convince my parents...

105
00:09:23,462 --> 00:09:26,198
What are you talking about?

106
00:09:28,924 --> 00:09:31,594
I want to run away from home

107
00:09:31,594 --> 00:09:36,528
Because of my aunt's parents, I became a mess.

108
00:09:36,528 --> 00:09:43,330
Even if my parents give me money, I can't use it freely, so I have 1 million.

109
00:09:43,330 --> 00:09:46,165
Then Auntie won't have to give up her inheritance either.

110
00:09:46,165 --> 00:09:49,858
It's cheap if you think of it as a nuisance fee.

111
00:09:50,957 --> 00:09:54,660
I don't know yet (Sakura) huh?

112
00:09:54,660 --> 00:09:58,495
I still don't know what really happened that day

113
00:09:58,495 --> 00:10:03,066
There are things that the police haven't investigated yet...

114
00:10:03,066 --> 00:10:05,858
what? What I haven't investigated

115
00:10:05,858 --> 00:10:09,891
(Sakura) Dad said he couldn't remember if there was anyone above him after all.

116
00:10:09,891 --> 00:10:13,264
Was the suicide note real?

117
00:10:14,264 --> 00:10:19,660
Anyway, give me a little more time

118
00:10:22,462 --> 00:10:24,264
Well, let's stay for a while.

119
00:10:24,264 --> 00:10:26,726
He came out saying he was staying with a friend.

120
00:10:26,726 --> 00:10:28,726
Huh?

121
00:10:30,792 --> 00:10:35,924
(Sakura) I don't want to stay home, I can't sleep.

122
00:10:35,924 --> 00:10:38,825
Huh?

123
00:10:38,825 --> 00:10:42,528
When I go out, even on foot, I have to wear a helmet.

124
00:10:42,528 --> 00:10:47,066
Because people might fall from above.

125
00:10:48,660 --> 00:10:55,396
Mom's crying in the middle of the night makes me feel sick and I can't sleep.

126
00:10:55,396 --> 00:11:04,792
♬〜

127
00:11:04,792 --> 00:11:07,099
(Taro) Because we played rock, paper, and scissors while spinning around.

128
00:11:07,099 --> 00:11:09,891
Really... isn't that it? Won't it get messy?

129
00:11:09,891 --> 00:11:12,561
(Sakura) What? that

130
00:11:12,561 --> 00:11:15,825
Ah... Okay, let's go.

131
00:11:15,825 --> 00:11:18,693
Are you okay? It's okay, just a little...

132
00:11:18,693 --> 00:11:22,957
Thank you, but it's such a coincidence.

133
00:11:22,957 --> 00:11:26,561
I'm really sorry I was surprised.

134
00:11:26,561 --> 00:11:29,396
no…

135
00:11:29,396 --> 00:11:36,429
I mean, the other day too... Huh?

136
00:11:36,429 --> 00:11:39,363
No... (sigh)

137
00:11:39,363 --> 00:11:44,924
Why do all these troublesome things happen?

138
00:11:44,924 --> 00:11:51,627
Ah, until I find out what the police said earlier...

139
00:11:51,627 --> 00:11:55,363
Ah... Huh?

140
00:11:55,363 --> 00:11:57,495
(sound of breathing)

141
00:11:57,495 --> 00:12:01,594
Does it smell like your mother?

142
00:12:01,594 --> 00:12:03,858
Right now...

143
00:12:03,858 --> 00:12:08,000
I washed and dried it properly the other day.

144
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:10,660
Hehehehe

145
00:12:20,000 --> 00:12:23,165
(Taro) Haha...

146
00:12:23,165 --> 00:12:28,660
Are you dating that girl? (Taro) Huh? Did it look like that?

147
00:12:28,660 --> 00:12:31,363
Wouldn't it be better to just stop?

148
00:12:31,363 --> 00:12:36,066
(Taro) Huh? It just doesn't seem to fit.

149
00:12:36,066 --> 00:12:41,165
And it seems like things are going to be tough right now (Taro), so I want to help.

150
00:12:41,165 --> 00:12:46,264
If I had money, it would be 1 million... Huh?

151
00:12:46,264 --> 00:12:52,924
Sister, if you're friends with that Mio, please convince me.

152
00:12:52,924 --> 00:12:55,000
Make sure to pay Kondo-san 1 million yen.

153
00:12:55,000 --> 00:12:57,000
Huh? (Taro) No, because

154
00:12:57,000 --> 00:13:03,264
Because of that person's parents, Kondo's father...

155
00:13:03,264 --> 00:13:07,825
I feel sorry for you, Mr. Kondo.

156
00:13:07,825 --> 00:13:15,000
No? So who's to blame?

157
00:13:18,660 --> 00:13:23,594
Anyway, my sister is against it.

158
00:13:23,594 --> 00:13:28,924
Sister, something has been weird for a while now.

159
00:13:28,924 --> 00:13:31,957
Did something happen with Kenken?

160
00:13:31,957 --> 00:13:37,594
Lately, I haven't come here at all, and I don't talk to you.

161
00:13:37,594 --> 00:13:42,396
Especially because we've already broken up

162
00:13:42,396 --> 00:13:45,198
Huh? Lie? when? why?

163
00:13:45,198 --> 00:13:52,066
There are a lot of things going on, like work and your food.

164
00:13:52,066 --> 00:13:57,132
I don't want to do all this love hustle.

165
00:13:57,132 --> 00:14:01,099
It kind of looks like my mom

166
00:14:01,099 --> 00:14:04,066
What does it mean?

167
00:14:04,066 --> 00:14:08,660
After all, I'm the one in the way.

168
00:14:08,660 --> 00:14:10,594
No, I didn't say that.

169
00:14:10,594 --> 00:14:14,627
I'm grateful to my sister

170
00:14:14,627 --> 00:14:18,759
Also about home...

171
00:14:18,759 --> 00:14:26,000
Dad, it's about when you died.

172
00:14:26,000 --> 00:14:31,528
But for me?

173
00:14:31,528 --> 00:14:39,792
It's really important that you keep using me as an excuse.

174
00:14:39,792 --> 00:14:49,396
♬〜

175
00:14:49,396 --> 00:14:54,693
(Sounds) Dad? (sound of tapping on table)

176
00:14:54,693 --> 00:14:59,033
Ah... sorry

177
00:14:59,033 --> 00:15:02,627
Yeah, it's delicious.

178
00:15:04,099 --> 00:15:07,231
You have a sticky mouth (lol)

179
00:15:07,231 --> 00:15:10,561
I'll go wash up in the bathroom and mom will be there soon.

180
00:15:10,561 --> 00:15:16,495
♬〜

181
00:15:16,495 --> 00:15:20,726
What? Are you going home yet? There are still some left though

182
00:15:20,726 --> 00:15:24,429
So tell me what you're hiding? Ah...

183
00:15:24,429 --> 00:15:27,693
Nothing in particular

184
00:15:27,693 --> 00:15:30,462
(sigh)

185
00:15:30,462 --> 00:15:33,957
You're still here, don't bother the earth.

186
00:15:33,957 --> 00:15:36,660
Eh, no, but...

187
00:15:36,660 --> 00:15:41,231
I promised you that when we got married, right?

188
00:15:41,231 --> 00:15:46,066
If I do something bad, I'll get divorced and I'll never see you again for the rest of my life.

189
00:15:46,066 --> 00:15:48,198
There was a time when I said "already" because there was nothing left.

190
00:15:48,198 --> 00:15:51,000
No, that's not it...

191
00:15:51,000 --> 00:15:56,297
♬〜

192
00:15:56,297 --> 00:15:59,858
(sound of things falling)

193
00:15:59,858 --> 00:16:02,330
Ah, sorry

194
00:16:04,099 --> 00:16:06,660
Ah...

195
00:16:36,825 --> 00:16:43,759
(cell phone vibration sound)

196
00:16:43,759 --> 00:16:50,561
Hello📱Ah, I'm glad it came out.

197
00:16:50,561 --> 00:16:56,099
Huh? 📱You know, about the other day...

198
00:16:56,099 --> 00:16:59,693
📱Sorry, breaking into a building or something.

199
00:16:59,693 --> 00:17:03,297
I almost made you a criminal.

200
00:17:03,297 --> 00:17:06,957
I was just thinking of apologizing properly.

201
00:17:06,957 --> 00:17:10,363
No, that's not it at all...

202
00:17:10,363 --> 00:17:15,495
📱I didn't hear from you, so I guess they cut me off.

203
00:17:18,066 --> 00:17:24,165
📱I'm sorry, that's all I wanted to say

204
00:17:24,165 --> 00:17:28,561
My head is full of infidelity 📱 huh?

205
00:17:29,891 --> 00:17:33,495
I found out that the person I was dating was having an affair.

206
00:17:33,495 --> 00:17:37,297
So I started having an affair in my head.

207
00:17:37,297 --> 00:17:39,891
I wasn't able to reply

208
00:17:39,891 --> 00:17:43,132
📱Wait a minute, is it an affair?

209
00:17:43,132 --> 00:17:50,726
So it's not like I was angry with Mio-chan or anything.

210
00:17:50,726 --> 00:17:56,264
📱Could you add something sweet?

211
00:17:56,264 --> 00:18:03,297
Huh? 📱I kind of want to see your face

212
00:18:04,330 --> 00:18:07,330
So what? What did you like about Kenken?

213
00:18:07,330 --> 00:18:10,693
Hmm absolutely what? I think that's what you say

214
00:18:10,693 --> 00:18:12,858
Yeah, definitely say what? That's what I say

215
00:18:12,858 --> 00:18:17,396
Hehehehe, there was a welcome party when I joined the company.

216
00:18:17,396 --> 00:18:20,066
It was a shop with horigotatsu, but I don't like horigotatsu.

217
00:18:20,066 --> 00:18:22,363
I'm going to sit straight.

218
00:18:22,363 --> 00:18:24,462
If you want to pick up chopsticks

219
00:18:24,462 --> 00:18:26,924
Kenken, who was sitting across from me, didn't have any legs.

220
00:18:26,924 --> 00:18:31,099
Ah, this person also sits straight.

221
00:18:31,099 --> 00:18:34,066
Yes? No... on the way home

222
00:18:34,066 --> 00:18:36,396
"Your feet are numb, right?" I was asked.

223
00:18:36,396 --> 00:18:39,330
Ah, I'm surprised you're actually looking at people.

224
00:18:39,330 --> 00:18:43,792
Fufufu No, but... No, but it's different.

225
00:18:43,792 --> 00:18:48,132
It was so nice to see this from diagonally below.

226
00:18:48,132 --> 00:18:50,330
The feeling around here hehehehe

227
00:18:50,330 --> 00:18:54,099
I'll wait and see. As expected, hahahaha

228
00:18:54,099 --> 00:18:58,858
Looking at people diagonally from below, that line is kind of nice, isn't it?

229
00:18:58,858 --> 00:19:01,165
Well, I watched it after I had cooled down...

230
00:19:01,165 --> 00:19:07,462
Yeah, I know, it's just a jaw, hehehehe

231
00:19:07,462 --> 00:19:11,759
Is that your younger brother Taro from earlier? Huh?

232
00:19:11,759 --> 00:19:14,264
You mean you ran away with that girl?

233
00:19:14,264 --> 00:19:16,429
Look, from the horrible mother I was talking about the other day.

234
00:19:16,429 --> 00:19:19,660
Yeah well that's right

235
00:19:19,660 --> 00:19:23,000
Since when did you ignore me after my father died?

236
00:19:23,000 --> 00:19:27,363
Well, a long time ago when I was a child

237
00:19:27,363 --> 00:19:30,429
Did he die from an illness?

238
00:19:31,561 --> 00:19:34,066
Police... Huh?

239
00:19:34,066 --> 00:19:38,330
There are things I haven't investigated yet.

240
00:19:38,330 --> 00:19:40,660
They didn't give me any details though

241
00:19:40,660 --> 00:19:45,198
Mr. Endo said he would try to investigate a little more.

242
00:19:45,198 --> 00:19:48,858
I can't help but understand how that girl, Sakura, feels.

243
00:19:48,858 --> 00:19:51,792
Suddenly I got caught up in something like this

244
00:19:51,792 --> 00:19:54,627
Well, I guess I can't stay at home all the time.

245
00:19:54,627 --> 00:19:59,231
I feel like I don't know what to do with 1 million.

246
00:20:00,264 --> 00:20:02,231
What does Mio-chan think now?

247
00:20:02,231 --> 00:20:04,429
About your mother

248
00:20:04,429 --> 00:20:09,594
Well, I don't think it was definitely suicide.

249
00:20:09,594 --> 00:20:12,396
But anyway, I want to know the truth

250
00:20:12,396 --> 00:20:16,000
What happened to your mother that day?

251
00:20:16,000 --> 00:20:19,000
If there is a possibility that there is someone above you

252
00:20:19,000 --> 00:20:21,330
I don't know if that person pushed it, right?

253
00:20:21,330 --> 00:20:24,033
But maybe he's saying something.

254
00:20:24,033 --> 00:20:28,099
The last moment with my mother

255
00:20:28,099 --> 00:20:31,891
